'''猶他州巨碑'''（{{lang-en|Utah monolith}}），又名'''猶他州金屬巨柱'''，是一根金屬柱子，矗立在美國[[猶他州|猶他州]][[聖胡安縣_(猶他州)|聖胡安縣]]東南部的紅色[[砂岩|砂岩]][[狹縫型峽谷|狹縫型峽谷]]中。這個9.5英尺（3米）高的結構是由金屬片鉚接而成的，組成為[[三角柱|三角柱狀]]。它在2016年7月至10月之間被不合法地放置在公共土地上。2020年11月，州份的生物學家們在一次坐直升機調查野生[[大角羊|大角羊]]時發現了它。

幾天內，公眾利用GPS繪圖軟件找到了巨碑，並前往這個偏遠的位置。不知道是誰製造這個巨碑，以及為何要製造，令人們對它進行猜測。在媒體報道「神秘巨碑吸引了全國人民」後，2020年11月27日它就被身份不明的四人團體暗中移走。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/01/arts/design/utah-monolith-removed-instagram.html |title = Earthlings, It Seems, Not Aliens, Removed the Utah Monolith |date = 2020-12-01 |publisher = The New York Times |language = en |access-date = 2020-12-02 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173228/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/01/arts/design/utah-monolith-removed-instagram.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/artist-or-aliens-mystery-surrounds-utah-monolith-s-appearance-disappearance-n1249424 |title = Artist or aliens? Mystery surrounds Utah monolith's appearance and disappearance |author = Ben Kesslen |date = 2020-12-01 |publisher = NBC News |language = en |access-date = 2020-12-02 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173200/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/artist-or-aliens-mystery-surrounds-utah-monolith-s-appearance-disappearance-n1249424 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

[[羅馬尼亞|羅馬尼亞]]、[[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]]、[[荷蘭|荷蘭]]和[[英國|英國]]也出現過類似的金屬柱子，羅馬尼亞與加利福尼亞州的巨碑後來被移走。

== 發現 ==
2020年11月18日，{{link-en|猶他州野生動植物資源局|Utah Division of Wildlife Resources}}的州份生物學家在猶他州東南部從直升機上調查[[大角羊|大角羊]]時，其中一名生物學家發現了這個結構物，並告訴飛行員Bret Hutchings再次飛過該地點。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/utah-monolith-art-trnd/index.html |title = Utah helicopter crew discovers mysterious metal monolith deep in the desert |author = Leah Asmelash |date = 2020-11-25 |publisher = CNN |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-11-24 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201124074434/https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/utah-monolith-art-trnd/index.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>Hutchings描繪發現的那一刻：

{{Quote|text=其中一個生物學家發現它，而我們剛好直接飛到它的上空。他說：「-{zh-hans:哇，哇，哇，回头！回头！;zh-tw:喔，喔，喔！回頭啊！回頭！;zh-hk:嘩，嘩，嘩，轉回頭，轉回頭！}-」，我問「-{zh-hans:什么;zh-tw:什麼;zh-hant:甚麼}-？」，他說「後面有東西——我們得去看看！」}}

Hutchings指出，該物體似乎是人造的，是「栽」在地上，而不是從天上掉下來的。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/23/helicopter-pilot-finds-strange-monolith-in-remote-part-of-utah |title = Helicopter pilot finds 'strange' monolith in remote part of Utah |author = Amanda Holpuch |date = 2020-11-24 |publisher = The Guardian |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-11-23 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201123231243/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/23/helicopter-pilot-finds-strange-monolith-in-remote-part-of-utah |dead-url = no }}</ref>

11月20日，{{link-en|猶他州公共安全部|Utah Department of Public Safety}}（DPS）在[[Instagram|Instagram]]上發布了該巨柱的照片。11月23日，DPS在其網站上發布了該物體的影片和照片，但沒有公布其具體位置，稱：「DPS的空勤局在紅岩國度（Red Rock Country）遭遇巨碑」。

== 內容 ==
[[File:Yatrides'_Slab.JPG|225px]] 
在第一次發現這個巨柱時，DPS將它形容為巨碑（monolith），此後其他主要媒體也重複了這一說法，雖然「[[磐石|巨碑]]」這個字眼指的是一塊巨大石頭，但這個字也與電影《[[2001太空漫遊_(電影)|2001太空漫遊]]》中的{{link-en|巨碑 (2001太空漫遊)|Monolith (Space Odyssey)|巨碑}}有著密切的聯系，與猶他州的巨碑有著相似之處。這個巨柱有[[鉚釘#抽芯鉚釘|盲鉚釘]]，被認為是人造的。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://reason.com/2020/11/24/giant-metal-monolith-discovered-in-utah-desert-possibly-extraterrestrial-definitely-a-code-violation/ |title = Giant Metal Monolith Discovered In Utah Desert Possibly Extraterrestrial, Definitely a Code Violation |author = Christian Britschgi |date = 2020-11-24 |publisher = Reason |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173232/https://reason.com/2020/11/24/giant-metal-monolith-discovered-in-utah-desert-possibly-extraterrestrial-definitely-a-code-violation/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>

== 合法性 ==
[[File:Vehicles_Parking_on_Vegetation_(Utah_monolith).jpg|thumb]]的照片說明「車輛停放在植物上，破壞靠近現場的資源」]]
DPS發表了聲明，引用[[美國內政部土地管理局|美國內政部土地管理局]]（BLM）的規定，未經許可在公共土地上安裝結構物（包括[[藝術|藝術品]]）是非法的，「不管你是來自哪個星球」。

== 被移除 ==
[[File:Missing_Monolith_(Utah_monolith).jpg|thumb]]
土地管理局的猶他州分部表示收到可靠報告稱，該巨碑已於2020年11月27日晚上被不明團體移走了，剩下的部份只是一塊曾經在頂部的三角形金屬片。兩位在接近午夜時分徒步前往該地點的人士Riccardo Marino和Sierra Van Meter說，當他們走近該地點時，看到一輛小型貨車載著一個物體駛離了現場。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/28/us/monolith-utah-disappeared.html |title = That Mysterious Monolith in the Utah Desert? It's Gone, Officials Say |author = Bryan Pietsch |date = 2020-11-29 |publisher = The New York Times |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173228/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/28/us/monolith-utah-disappeared.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/mysterious-monolith-rural-utah-has-vanished-officials-say-n1249272 |title = Mysterious monolith in rural Utah has vanished, officials say |author = Kalhan Rosenblatt |date = 2020-11-29 |publisher = NBC News |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173230/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/mysterious-monolith-rural-utah-has-vanished-officials-say-n1249272 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.sltrib.com/news/2020/11/28/utahs-desert-obelisk-has/ |title = Utah's desert obelisk has disappeared |date = 2020-11-28 |publisher = The Salt Lake Tribune |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-11-29 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129061555/https://www.sltrib.com/news/2020/11/28/utahs-desert-obelisk-has/ |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/29/monolith-vanishes-from-utah-desert |title = Mystery metal monolith vanishes from Utah desert |author = Kenya Evelyn |date = 2020-11-29 |publisher = The Guardian |language = en |access-date = 2020-11-30 |archive-date = 2020-11-29 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129170249/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/nov/29/monolith-vanishes-from-utah-desert |dead-url = no }}</ref>

2020年12月1日，《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》報道了更多關於四名男子拆除和移走巨碑的細節（和圖片），幾位冒險攝影師（包括Ross Bernards、Peter Jans和Michael James Newlands）見證這件事，並發佈在[[Instagram|Instagram]]上。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.instagram.com/p/CIOOkwMBkAS/ |title = Ross Bernard - Instagram |author = Ross Bernards |date = 2020-11-30 |publisher = Instagram |language = en |access-date = 2020-12-02 |archive-date = 2020-12-02 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201202234846/https://www.instagram.com/p/CIOOkwMBkAS/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>12月1日，有一段影片被發佈在YouTube上，名為「我們移走了猶他州巨碑」（We Removed the Utah monolith）。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r6c2EhNtSj4&ab_channel=MrSlackline |title = We REMOVED the Utah Monolith. |date = 2020-12-01 |publisher = YouTube |language = en}}</ref>影片顯示四名人士用手推車運走該結構物。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.sltrib.com/news/2020/12/01/moabs-mr-slackline-claims/ |title = Moab's ‘Mr. Slackline’ claims he was behind the removal of the Utah monolith |author = Zak Podmore |date = 2020-12-01 |publisher = The Salt Lake Tribune |language = en |access-date = 2020-12-03 |archive-date = 2020-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201216173217/https://www.sltrib.com/news/2020/12/01/moabs-mr-slackline-claims/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>

